  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I remove adware and spyware virus?",
  "response": "Removing adware and spyware from your computer involves a few steps. Here\u2019s a straightforward guide to help you clean your system:\n\n### 1. **Disconnect From the Internet**\nThis prevents the malware from sending out any additional data or downloading more malicious programs.\n\n### 2. **Enter Safe Mode**\nRestart your computer and press F8 (or Shift + Restart for Windows 10). Choose 'Safe Mode with Networking' to limit the startups to essential services, which can sometimes prevent the malware from running.\n\n### 3. **Check Installed Programs**\nGo to Control Panel > Programs and Features and uninstall any suspicious programs. Common sources of adware/spyware might include toolbars, \u201cfree\u201d software, or programs you do not recognize.\n\n### 4. **Run Antivirus and Antispyware Scans**\nInstall and run reputable antivirus and antispyware software. Here are some recommended tools:\n- **Malwarebytes**: Effective at detecting and removing malware.\n- **AdwCleaner**: Specifically targets adware.\n- **Spybot Search and Destroy**: Effective for removing spyware and other threats.\n- **SuperAntiSpyware**: Good for comprehensive scanning and removal.\n\n### 5. **Use Browser Cleaning Tools**\nAdware often hides in browser extensions or adds home pages/search engines:\n- **Chrome**: Go to Settings > Extensions and remove any suspicious extensions.\n- **Firefox**: Go to Add-ons > Extensions and remove suspicious items.\n- Reset browser settings if needed.\n\n### 6. **Manual Cleaning**\nCheck the following directories for unusual files:\n- **Windows Temp Folder**: (`C:\\Windows\\Temp`)\n- **User Temp Folder**: (`C:\\Users\\[Your Username]\\AppData\\Local\\Temp`)\n- **Program Data Folder**: (`C:\\ProgramData`)\n- **AppData Folder**: Remove suspicious directories intertwined in (`C:\\Users\\[Your Username]\\AppData\\Local` and `C:\\Users\\[Your Username]\\AppData\\Roaming`).\n\n### 7. **Update Your Software**\nEnsure your operating system, browsers, and all software are up-to-date. This minimizes security vulnerabilities that could be exploited by malware.\n\n### 8. **Reset Network Settings**\nIf you've been having persistent issues:\n- Windows: `Settings > Network and internet > Network reset`.\n\n### 9. **Professional Help**\nIf all else fails, consider taking your computer to a professional technician.\n\n### **Prevention Tips:**\n- **Install an Ad-blocker**: Use browser extensions to block ads.\n- **Be Cautious**: Avoid downloading/installing software from unknown sources.\n- **Regular Scans**: Schedule regular antivirus and antispyware scans.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to effectively remove adware and spyware from your computer and protect against future infections.",
